<subSubSection id="941445C59F9CCC89CC1CD1C41013AF6B" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0D85FAF9C015EC52625255BCAA53B5FE" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D8126E06A32234276C773E86BE4C1011" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="57EFF79ED17D2F74B038FCE87284C91B" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. erlangping" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erlangping">
<emphasis id="0553BBD6740D51593F8AA76FF8E9A34C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. erlangping</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="2C24F982B2D4CE90312FEFA88B618167" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. heteroidea" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heteroidea">
<emphasis id="AEB5399EB75C87CCCBE9AB0AF14A5281" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. heteroidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distiguished from the latter by the tegulum having one curved furrow (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9AF214A721CE66D4CDE0221CD4068FF0" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genital anatomy of Portia erlangping sp. nov. A-D HN- 013 - 001 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606780" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">3A</figureCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName id="9BE370C9D91382DE6CD785D9E9454F8B" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. heteroidea" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heteroidea">
<emphasis id="7E378DD9C6284B75830CE3F13F1D3516" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. heteroidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two furrows (see fig. 6 in 
<bibRefCitation id="0371CAC3422CDD5410C6E50FD05B3EFA" author="Xie, LP" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="30 - 34" refId="B13" refString="Xie, LP, Yin, CM, 1991. Two new species of Salticidae from China (Arachnida: Araneae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica 16: 30 - 34" title="Two new species of Salticidae from China (Arachnida: Araneae)." volume="16" year="1991">Xie and Yin (1991)</bibRefCitation>
), and by the longer cymbium flange (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0BBE83494770B7FE037948B94B676D74" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genital anatomy of Portia erlangping sp. nov. A-D HN- 013 - 001 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606780" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">3D</figureCitation>
; see fig. 8 in 
<bibRefCitation id="E8CD70B7F01C674E990D93FE1AD3DB3F" author="Xie, LP" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="30 - 34" refId="B13" refString="Xie, LP, Yin, CM, 1991. Two new species of Salticidae from China (Arachnida: Araneae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica 16: 30 - 34" title="Two new species of Salticidae from China (Arachnida: Araneae)." volume="16" year="1991">Xie and Yin (1991)</bibRefCitation>
); from those of 
<taxonomicName id="979557E55CC50CD3541960129911576E" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. albimana" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimana">
<emphasis id="887861B7735833EB8034D6852DDF07A8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. albimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the longer embolus, larger cymbium flange and thicker retrolateral tibial apophysis (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B1B25607DFCFD78337788B5A8D408AB9" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genital anatomy of Portia erlangping sp. nov. A-D HN- 013 - 001 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606780" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">3A, D</figureCitation>
; see fig. 12B-D in 
<bibRefCitation id="5C8FD92F3F0A64E3FE50313CFCAA38CE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" author="Wanless, FR" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology)" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="83 - 124" refId="B14" refString="Wanless, FR, 1978. A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae). Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 34: 83 - 124, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" title="A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" volume="34" year="1978">Wanless (1978)</bibRefCitation>
); from those of 
<taxonomicName id="46AC857B34203B075F3DD6ECA0B60FFB" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. assamensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="assamensis">
<emphasis id="13655282B97D3BCBF9E2B09886BAA3C3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. assamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7157744E034AE9CBC1E729CCE04902FC" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. fimbriata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fimbriata">
<emphasis id="4ED56321800DF3F530ABABCD3C2819F6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. fimbriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="12ABAA55F697315C1E213F64CF7E3918" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. labiata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis id="C40ACF2FB897A8E2AB6DFB3A02C7512E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. labiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A934E035AED0759E5D9F967247953620" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. orientalis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="7A2897E88E7789DBB6A3B7D1910D2B96" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="74AB10513D56D8722BBC2C23763A21F2" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. quei" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quei">
<emphasis id="C1580DBDE9B1A05DDA80F840C6DE6D29" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. quei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EB26490E29AA5E174BC6E8FD79299866" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. xishan" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xishan">
<emphasis id="3BC00B548E296B3140FF729A3EEDAE6D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. xishan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName id="AF4A6C225FEA46828055CAC572D0FE55" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. taiwanica" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiwanica">
<emphasis id="476F7D9903ED0E888CF83B01391E342B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. taiwanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="87805ADA88561BB783994B6D97F1DB88" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. zhaoi" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhaoi">
<emphasis id="4950B8C8C8729913A22F1F505DEA2C2D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. zhaoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the embolus being shortest (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="59201A7148DBDE1FDE6A1FC6DABCCEF2" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genital anatomy of Portia erlangping sp. nov. A-D HN- 013 - 001 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606780" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">3A</figureCitation>
; see figs 10D, 7C, and10A in 
<bibRefCitation id="D6230F6447D3F52390B084FEB643B9B9" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" author="Wanless, FR" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology)" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="83 - 124" refId="B14" refString="Wanless, FR, 1978. A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae). Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 34: 83 - 124, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" title="A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" volume="34" year="1978">Wanless (1978)</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 6 in 
<bibRefCitation id="8F13E90ED3A56039516B59F6E054757B" author="Murphy, J" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="37 - 45" refId="B8" refString="Murphy, J, Murphy, F, 1983. More about Portia (Araneae: Salticidae). Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society 6: 37 - 45" title="More about Portia (Araneae: Salticidae)." volume="6" year="1983">Murphy and Murphy 1983</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 661 in 
<bibRefCitation id="BC7D90D5AFD42D03AEF5E54F7F783E33" author="Peng, XJ" journalOrPublisher="Hunan Normal University Press, Changsha" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" refId="B11" refString="Peng, XJ, Xie, LP, Xiao, XQ, Yin, CM, 1993. Salticids in China (Arachnida: Araneae). Hunan Normal University Press, Changsha" title="Salticids in China (Arachnida: Araneae)." year="1993">Peng et al. (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, and fig. 4B in 
<bibRefCitation id="CE5C7888253364AD437E84AD5758E66F" DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4619118" author="Zhang, JX" journalOrPublisher="Raffles Bulletin of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="221 - 229" refId="B16" refString="Zhang, JX, Li, D, 2005. Four new and one newly recorded species of the jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae: Lyssomaninae &amp; Spartaeinae) from (sub)tropical China. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology 53: 221 - 229, DOI: http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4619118" title="Four new and one newly recorded species of the jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae: Lyssomaninae &amp; Spartaeinae) from (sub) tropical China." url="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4619118" volume="53" year="2005">Zhang and Li (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, respectively); in addition, from those of 
<taxonomicName id="B98A17663D20BF3E809128A6025A3A93" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. assamensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="assamensis">
<emphasis id="12B4231DE96A6FF7FDF5927FB414088B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. assamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="44B99EB7B362A07354907794987F29CA" class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. fimbriata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fimbriata">
<emphasis id="C40C41D7F0CCDC836853ADE088ED8684" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. fimbriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the cymbium flange being thickest and longest (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7B8E0A2515D2208CEF988AE72F33AF06" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genital anatomy of Portia erlangping sp. nov. A-D HN- 013 - 001 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606780" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">3D</figureCitation>
