<subSubSection id="9F8977CBBA01C06C24EF06E156750E65" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph id="C483F6FF4751B7D18B6D70C16B57B9A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="533F9D704906D4F865A81A369F883AC1" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="FDEBF5DC410F07AF522AC221DE14FEFB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Male</emphasis>
(holotype). Carapace greyish brown with white band on thoracic groove and lateral margin. Ocular area yellow-brown, with tufts of yellow-brown hairs around AME. Clypeus black-brown without dense ventral white hairs. Chelicerae dark brown with 2 small promarginal and 3 large retromarginal teeth. Maxillae and labium black-brown with white anterior margin. Sternum black-brown, densely covered with creamy white hairs. Measurements: eye sizes: AME 0.64, ALE 0.24, PME 0.17, PLE 0.21, anterior eye row 1.78 wide, posterior eye row 1.65 wide, eye area 1.38 long; clypeus height 0.30; BL 5.84-6.45; holotype BL 5.84, CL 2.89, CW 2.14, AL 2.95, AW 1.60; leg I 8.40 (2.25 + 0.92 + 2.02 + 2.11 + 1.10), leg II 6.95 (1.90 + 0.94 + 1.57 + 1.60 + 0.94), leg III 6.46 (1.92 + 0.74 + 1.30 + 1.72 + 0.78), leg IV 9.45 (2.47 + 0.97 + 2.06 + 2.94 + 1.01). Leg formula 4123. Legs black-brown, slender, ventral portion of tibiae fringed with long black hairs. Dorsum of abdomen black-brown, anterior portion light brown with grey-white hairs, middle portion with a small triangular patch and posterior portion with two oval patches, the three patches densely covered with grey-white hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="062C8427A5C98A998EFD01A5249A7875" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
Palp. Tibia with 3 apophyses, ventral one thick and short, intermediate one relatively slender, retrolateral one largest and bar-shaped in dorsal view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7EA7D196EBFF6F51C9B4B261C9653850" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genital anatomy of Portia erlangping sp. nov. A-D HN- 013 - 001 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606780" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">3A-D</figureCitation>
). Embolus short and stout (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="816C645382E4DD00DDDEC89BBA1532B8" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genital anatomy of Portia erlangping sp. nov. A-D HN- 013 - 001 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606780" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">3A</figureCitation>
). Seminal duct clear and S-shaped. Tegulum with a deeply curved furrow and a membraneous apophysis (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B66562631DB3C3B51E32DC53047C7ACF" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genital anatomy of Portia erlangping sp. nov. A-D HN- 013 - 001 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606780" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">3A, B</figureCitation>
). Cymbium flange robust, terminal portion overlapping on base of retrolateral tibial apophysis dorsally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F9479FB4D495F8223D0E4F5ACD79C9D0" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genital anatomy of Portia erlangping sp. nov. A-D HN- 013 - 001 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606780" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">3D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
